race.comment: FARMOR BACARDI (3) hit the ground running and set it up early last time, clocking 19.43 with a 3.5 lengths win at this track over 352m and making it back to back wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Can continue on her winning ways. UNTAMED VELOCITY (7) could not have been more impressive last start in her slick 19.74 win at this track in a Grade 5 over 352m. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. HUCKLEBERRY HUGO (8) recorded his best time this course and distance last start, taking a Grade 5 in 19.53 by a nose. Has the ability and looks a key chance. MR. O'MALLEY (2) is worth including after a top-three finish from the same draw most recently. Something for the Multiples: FARMOR JACUZZIS (4)
